The paper discusses a method for estimating unnormalized statistical models, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method, called sliced score matching, is designed to be scalable and applicable to complex models and high-dimensional data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which further support these sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) to prove the consistency and asymptotic normality of the estimators, which suggests that this sub-category is also relevant.
